# Force text handling for this repo's plain-text source files so a future
# git binary-content-detection false positive (e.g. a stray NUL byte, an
# unusual Unicode sequence) can't silently break `git diff`/merge on them.
# This is defense-in-depth, not a fix for a live bug: the one incident that
# actually tripped git's binary heuristic here — a literal NUL byte embedded
# in a template-literal sentinel in lib/installed-plugins.mjs — has already
# been fixed at the source (the NUL byte is now a proper `\0` escape). Kept
# narrow to the extensions this repo's source actually uses; not an attempt
# to cover every possible file type.
*.mjs text
*.js text
*.md text
*.sh text
*.json text
